1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,170
Successfully resist the temptation to argue and quarrel by 1.

2
00:00:05,599 --> 00:00:11,409
Asking yourself, honestly now, is this thing really important enough to argue about?

3
00:00:11,409 --> 00:00:12,289
2.

4
00:00:12,639 --> 00:00:18,929
Reminding yourself you never gain anything from an argument, but you always lose something.

5
00:00:19,839 --> 00:00:27,250
Think big enough to see that quarrels, arguments, feuds, and fusses will never help you get where you want to go.

6
00:00:28,239 --> 00:00:32,289
D. When you feel defeated, think big.

7
00:00:32,719 --> 00:00:42,289
It is not possible to achieve large success without hardships and setbacks, but it is possible to live the rest of your life without defeat.

8
00:00:42,639 --> 00:00:45,889
Big thinkers react to setbacks this way.

9
00:00:45,889 --> 00:00:47,570
1.

10
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:50,130
Regard the setback as a lesson.

11
00:00:50,239 --> 00:00:51,170
Research it.

12
00:00:51,359 --> 00:00:53,490
Use it to propel you forward.

13
00:00:53,679 --> 00:00:56,210
Salvage something from every setback.

14
00:00:56,719 --> 00:00:58,130
2.

15
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:01,329
Blend persistence with experimentation.

16
00:01:01,519 --> 00:01:04,929
Back off and start afresh with a new approach.

17
00:01:06,079 --> 00:01:11,170
Think big enough to see that defeat is a state of mind, nothing more.

18
00:01:12,079 --> 00:01:16,769
E. When romance starts to slip, think big.

19
00:01:17,519 --> 00:01:25,329
Negative, petty, she's-he's-unfair-to-me-so-I'll-get-even type of thinking slaughters romance,

20
00:01:25,519 --> 00:01:28,369
destroys the affection that can be yours.

21
00:01:28,719 --> 00:01:32,690
Do this when things aren't going right in the love department.

22
00:01:32,690 --> 00:01:34,369
1.

23
00:01:34,719 --> 00:01:39,090
Concentrate on the biggest qualities in the person you want to love you.

24
00:01:39,359 --> 00:01:42,849
Put little things where they belong, in second place.

25
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:48,050
Two, do something special for your mate and do it often.

26
00:01:48,799 --> 00:01:52,849
Think big enough to find the secret to marital joys.

27
00:01:54,079 --> 00:01:59,889
F, when you feel your progress on the job is slowing down, think big.

28
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:07,809
No matter what you do and regardless of your occupation, higher status, higher pay come from one thing,

29
00:02:08,079 --> 00:02:11,570
increasing the quality and quantity of your output.

30
00:02:11,839 --> 00:02:12,769
Do this.

31
00:02:13,199 --> 00:02:15,409
Think, I can do better.

32
00:02:15,759 --> 00:02:17,970
The best is not unattainable.

33
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:20,530
There is room for doing everything better.

34
00:02:20,719 --> 00:02:24,530
Nothing in this world is being done as well as it could be.

35
00:02:24,799 --> 00:02:30,050
And when you think, I can do better, ways to do better will appear.

36
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:34,849
Thinking, I can do better, switches on your creative power.

37
00:02:35,359 --> 00:02:41,889
Think big enough to see that if you put service first, money takes care of itself.

38
00:02:42,559 --> 00:02:49,250
In the words of Publilius Cyrus, a wise man will be master of his mind,

39
00:02:49,519 --> 00:02:52,450
a fool will be its slave.
